Though my nation is called "Stratocratic-Anarchy Oceanic Empire", it's not actually 'anarchist' nor 'stratocratic'; not even an "empire". Oceania is a federal union of several constituent states with a president, a large legislature, and a democratic constitution. However, the nation was once the center of ideological strife between ideological factions. Hence this is why the Oceanic Mainland (the main landmass of Oceania) is split into two regions: "Anarchia" which consists of the eastern half of the Oceanic mainland. "Stratocratia" is the western half of the Oceanic Mainland.

Gralov wrote:
Stratocratic-Anarchy Oceanic Empire wrote:The Catgirl Republic continues to build closer ties with the capuchin with the opening of schools teaching the languages and tongues utilized by both polities. The Catgirl Aerospace Traversement Security Organization (CATSO) has finalized the formation of the Catgirl's colony on the moon of Saturn, Titan. In a referendum by the small but growing populace of Titan by the mixed population of Catgirls and a small number of ethnic Martians, the Titan Republic is formed as an autonomous polity within the Catgirl Republic, however, fiscal policy and suzerainty remain in control by the Catgirl Republic due to the small size of Titan and its inability to defend itself and the necessary supplies it needs from the Catgirl state.

The Republic's military remains well prepared in case of aggression from surrounding Martian factions. However, relative peace reigns within the Catgirls as they focus on the wellbeing of their state hoping to remove the sins and crimes from the Martians due to their experiments that created their race. Massive developments continue to be made in the underground infrastructure of the Catgirls, more underground cities are made which grow in population from cloned Catgirls and the immigration of Martians fleeing from the war-torn factions of the planet.

Titan grows as a colony, its incredible conditions for the settlement of a civilization prove it to be a valuable asset to the Catgirls in closer connection to their allies on Earth, which at the moment only remains with the capuchin and his polity. However, a squadron of space-exploring Catgirls of CATSO during an expedition to study the atmosphere of Earth—mostly concerned about the Keppler Syndrome—the spaceship used by the squadron ends up crashing with space debris, causing them to crash land on Earth.

As the ship passes into the Earth's stratosphere, the ship captain jerks the small ship's flight stick and uses the remaining functions of its afterburners to land the ship in the Pacific Ocean. Things seem safe and so the crew begins attempts to make contact with the Catgirl embassy at the capuchin's island, however, the ship is lifted up by a wave of water and hits a sand bar which damages the engine and remaining functional parts of the ship immobile.

Prayers and patience pass through the Catgirl crew as they continue making contact with the embassy. But they are cut off as green-uniformed soldiers arrive and surround their ship. The Catgirl captain identifies the crew as an exploration squadron of the Catgirl Republic, a foreign country in space, but the soldiers arrest them anyway.

One of the squadron members, M'yri'ah notes the strange society developed in Hawaii within the city of Honolulu. It's very militaristic in many aspects. The military seems to have established a permanent military government on the island. She spends weeks in prison with the others as they continue awaiting aid from the Catgirl government, and through talks with the soldiers, they eventually learn that Hawaii has become a militaristic martial law government after the loss of contact with its mainland government.

Through tense negotiation with Hawaii, the prisoners are liberated. But M'yri'ah can't feel anything but sympathy as she looks at civilians squatting on the streets in poverty and the broken infrastructure littering the streets. This wasn't home for people.

With enough talk and debate. M'yri'ah reaches an audience with the parliament of the Republic. She gets into a passionate and persuasive speech of the duty of the Catgirl Republic to help defend the watered down and unprotected peoples on Earth. Believing that if the Catgirls managed to survive and succeed as a race created by brutal experiments and horrible treatment by the Martians, then the Catgirls have an obligation morally to help the people suffering on Earth.

M'yri'ah walks out of the halls of parliament with her heart still torn but hopeful for the government to accept this plea.

She waited a week, then two, then three.

Then parliament and the executive government agreed.

M'yri'ah's heart lifted up in joy.

They were going to Earth.

Through much strife and reform, Hawaii now has formed the Republic of Hawaiʻi (Hawaii). And a bright hope looms for the island. Reflections are made in its history. But M'yri'ah hopes for them to succeed this time with the aid of a fellow ally from space.

It takes a while but the martial law ends and the military finds itself no longer needed for administrative duties. An attempt to establish a junta by more extremist and high-ranking American military officers was made, but Hawaiian civilians of all colors banded together and fought back, resecuring Honolulu and ending the attempt of the attempted junta coup.

Now Hawaii remains growing. Having finally taken full administration of the remaining islands in the Hawaiian archipelago and also annexing the Johnston Atoll and Midway Islands with some aid from the Catgirls. But there's barely any population in these new lands as most of the people died from starvation or were left to find better homes elsewhere. Only a handful of people remained.

The Catgirls take full obligation in protecting the Republic of Hawai'i but they don't control its administrative or fiscal functions whatsoever. But they do have treaties with it.

by Stratocratic-Anarchy Oceanic Empire » Fri Jan 28, 2022 8:42 pm

The Catgirl Republic has finished constructing the Mow'lasa Line, a defensive line of artillery, walls, bunkers, tunnels, and fortifications to defend the surrounding borders of the Republic. This'll hopefully be helpful in deterring a ground invasion by surrounding Martian factions should an event like that arise.

But the fears of war were true. Images through satellites orbiting Mars and other reconnaissance technology showed that the two factions on Mars, the Ra'ki—dwarf size creatures with orange skin and a humanoid body of orange scales like a lizard—and the Nal'xiso—fifteen-foot tall creatures with eight thin legs (like an arachnid) that hold their round circular body and four arms, and they have light amounts of fur and hair on their body and their head is hunchbacked from the front of their body—were moving ground troops close to the Catgirl borders in the tens of thousands. Ra'ki military spaceships were spotted intimidating exiting Catgirl merchant vessels from Titan and Mars which continued to build up tensions amongst the nations.

M'yri'ah now a top diplomat and explorer of the Catgirl Republic was sent to the Ra'ki capital for peace negotiations but things immediately went downhill as the Ra'ki began citing their religious texts of the Catgirls as being false "abominations" that were mistakenly created by the Martians. And that they should be destroyed to remove them from existing at all. M'yri'ah is then forced out of the city of Ra'ki and disappointedly realizes that war is in the mist.

Nal'xiso spaceships start harassing Catgirl vessels in the asteroid belt, leading to a skirmish between some of the vessels wishing to defend themselves and the Nal'xiso ships worried the Catgirls are threatening their asteroid mining bases. This becomes the last straw and immediately the Nal'xiso and Ra'ki declare war and start offensives. The two Martian factions continue to attempt to get other factions involved in the conflict but for now, it remains them vs the Catgirls.

Fighting rages hard as the Catgirls not only fight for their independence but also their right to exist. The Mow'lasa Line holds itself quite well as the Catgirls utilizing the southern Martian highlands to bombard and send loads of highly explosive artillery shells to suppress the offensive Martian soldiers. The Ra'ki find themselves forced undercover and instead focus on a policy of tunneling to avoid the Catgirl defenses. Nal'xiso military forces focus themselves on fighting the Catgirls in the air and also in space, with major dogfights fought within the asteroid belt utilizing light fighter spaceships to weave through the belt for sortie missions.

Things remain in a stalemate so far but the Catgirls plan a major counteroffensive to drive back the two Martian factions in order to dissuade the other Martian factions from joining the war, making things easier for the Republic.
